@startuml IncidentFlowSequenceCritical
title IncidentFlow - Sequence: CRITICAL Incident Creation & Escalation

actor Operator
participant Frontend
participant "API\n(FastAPI)" as API
participant "Application\nLayer" as App
participant Database
participant "Event Bus" as EventBus
actor Commander
actor Manager

Operator -> Frontend: Create CRITICAL incident\n(title, description, severity)
Frontend -> API: POST /incidents\n{severity: CRITICAL}
API -> App: CreateIncident(incident_data)
App -> App: validate_incident()
App -> Database: save(incident)
Database --> App: incident_id
App -> EventBus: publish(INCIDENT_CREATED)
EventBus --> App: ✓

alt CRITICAL Severity
  App -> EventBus: publish(NOTIFY_COMMANDER)
  EventBus --> CommanderNotifications: queue notification
  App -> EventBus: publish(NOTIFY_MANAGER)
  EventBus --> ManagerNotifications: queue notification
else
  note over EventBus: Non-CRITICAL incidents\ndon't notify immediately
end

App --> API: {id, state: OPEN, severity: CRITICAL}
API --> Frontend: 201 Created
Frontend --> Operator: ✓ Incidente creado

note over Commander: Receives immediate\nnotification (push/banner)
note over Manager: Receives immediate\nnotification (push/banner)

Commander -> Frontend: View incident details
Frontend -> API: GET /incidents/{id}
API -> Database: fetch(incident)
Database --> API: incident_data
API --> Frontend: incident_details
Frontend --> Commander: Display incident

Commander -> Frontend: Assign to responder\nChange to ASSIGNED
Frontend -> API: PATCH /incidents/{id}/state\n{state: ASSIGNED, assignee_id: X}

API -> App: TransitionState(incident, ASSIGNED, commander_user)
App -> App: validate_transition()\n(checks: not CLOSED, has_assignee)
App -> Database: update(incident.state = ASSIGNED)
App -> Database: create_audit_log(who, what, when)
App -> EventBus: publish(INCIDENT_ASSIGNED)

EventBus --> Responder: notify(assigned_to_incident)
API --> Frontend: 200 OK
Frontend --> Commander: ✓ Estado actualizado

Responder -> Frontend: Start working
Frontend -> API: PATCH /incidents/{id}/state\n{state: IN_PROGRESS}
API -> App: TransitionState(IN_PROGRESS, responder_user)
App -> App: validate_transition()
App -> Database: update(incident.state = IN_PROGRESS)
App -> EventBus: publish(INCIDENT_IN_PROGRESS)

Responder -> Frontend: Add comment with resolution
Frontend -> API: POST /incidents/{id}/comments\n{text: "Fixed by restarting service X"}
API -> App: AddComment(incident_id, comment_text, user)
App -> Database: create_comment()
App -> Database: create_audit_log()
App -> EventBus: publish(COMMENT_ADDED)

Responder -> Frontend: Resolve incident
Frontend -> API: PATCH /incidents/{id}/state\n{state: RESOLVED, summary: "..."}
API -> App: TransitionState(RESOLVED, responder)
App -> Database: update(incident.state = RESOLVED)
App -> EventBus: publish(INCIDENT_RESOLVED)

EventBus --> ManagerNotifications: notify(incident_resolved)

Commander -> Frontend: Close incident\n(only Commander/Admin can do this)
Frontend -> API: PATCH /incidents/{id}/state\n{state: CLOSED}

API -> App: TransitionState(CLOSED, commander)
App -> App: validate_transition()\nif CRITICAL: require summary ✓
App -> Database: update(incident.state = CLOSED)
App -> Database: create_audit_log()
App -> EventBus: publish(INCIDENT_CLOSED)

EventBus --> ManagerNotifications: notify(incident_closed)
API --> Frontend: 200 OK

Frontend --> Commander: ✓ Incident closed\nTimeline & audit logged

@enduml
